Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil for the potatoes.

Trim the @butternut squash{1}, halve lengthways, then scoop out the seeds (peel first if you prefer). Cut into 1-2cm chunks.

Pop the diced butternut onto a large #baking tray{}.

Sprinkle the butternut with half of the @curry powder mix{1%sachet}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

In the meantime, chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer). Peel the @garlic{2%cloves}.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the potatoes and garlic and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @korma curry paste{50%g}, @tomato puree{30%g} and remaining curry powder. Fry for ~{1%minute}, until fragrant.

Pour the @creme fraiche{75%g}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{100%ml} into the pan. Bring to the boil, then simmer until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once the veg has roasted, stir it into the sauce. Taste, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Preheat your #grill{} to high. Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Once the potatoes and garlic are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{1%knob} and a splash of @milk{} (if you have any) and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

Transfer the korma mixture to an appropriately-sized #ovenproof dish{}. Top with the mash, using the back of a #spoon{} to smooth it out. Sprinkle over the cheese, then grill until golden and bubbling, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{80%g}. Wipe out the saucepan.

Pour the boiled water into the (now empty) saucepan with @salt{0.5%tsp} and heat on high.

Bring the water back to the boil, then add the green beans and cook until just tender, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a colander, then return to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Toss in @olive oil{}.

When everything's ready, divide the korma pie between your plates.

Serve with the green beans on the side. Enjoy!